Context:
The pruneStaleState function is called at the end of every reload (both performReload and performConfigReload). At line 128-134:
```ts
// Keep only outdatedPlugins entries for still-present plugins
const npmPkgNames = new Set(
  Array.from(state.registry.plugins.values())
    .map(p => p.npmPackageName)
    .filter((n): n is string => n !== undefined),
);
state.outdatedPlugins = state.outdatedPlugins.filter(o => npmPkgNames.has(o.name));
```

This only checks existence. After `updatePlugin()` runs `npm update` and `onReload()` rebuilds the registry with the new version, the stale OutdatedPlugin entry persists because the npm package name still exists.

The OutdatedPlugin interface (state.ts line 197-202):
```ts
export interface OutdatedPlugin {
  name: string;          // npm package name (e.g., '@opentabs-dev/opentabs-plugin-grafana')
  currentVersion: string;
  latestVersion: string;
  updateCommand: string;
}
```

The RegisteredPlugin interface has `version: string` (state.ts line 98) and `npmPackageName?: string` (check state.ts for exact line).

Changes:
Build a Map from npmPackageName to installed version, then filter by both existence AND version match:
```ts
const npmPkgVersions = new Map(
  Array.from(state.registry.plugins.values())
    .filter((p): p is typeof p & { npmPackageName: string } => p.npmPackageName !== undefined)
    .map(p => [p.npmPackageName, p.version]),
);
state.outdatedPlugins = state.outdatedPlugins.filter(
  o => npmPkgVersions.has(o.name) && npmPkgVersions.get(o.name) !== o.latestVersion,
);
```

This preserves the existing behavior (removed plugins are pruned) while also pruning entries where the version now matches.

Unit tests to add in reload.test.ts (after the existing 'filters outdatedPlugins to only include still-present npm packages' test at line 324):

1. 'prunes outdatedPlugins entry when installed version matches latestVersion': Create a plugin, reload to populate registry. Manually patch the registered plugin's npmPackageName and version to '2.0.0'. Add an outdated entry with latestVersion '2.0.0'. Reload. Assert outdatedPlugins is empty.

2. 'retains outdatedPlugins entry when installed version is still older': Same setup but plugin version stays '1.0.0' with latestVersion '2.0.0'. Reload. Assert outdatedPlugins has length 1.

Note: When patching RegisteredPlugin fields in tests, use `(plugin as unknown as Record<string, unknown>).field = value` to satisfy TypeScript's strict type checking.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the OutdatedPlugin interface
- Do NOT change how outdated entries are detected (version-check.ts) — only how stale entries are pruned
- The existing test at line 324 must still pass — it tests local plugins (no npmPackageName) which should still be pruned
- Update the comment above the filter to reflect the new behavior
